parameters: Hmph, how naive. To think this level of attack would...!

You've misjudged us as mere common travelers, and that was
your downfall. Before you commit any more evil deeds, I'll
annihilate you right here and now. Prepare yourself!!
Hey! Akane! One's headed your way! Be careful!
Oh! What splendid agility!
00_st_akane02_nomal

Akane: Pretty good, right? Well, I'm better at running away
than fighting, to be honest.

Ha ha ha, that's good. Even if one has combat skills, if
they misjudge the difference in strength, they can't be
called powerful. In that sense, Akane, you could be
considered quite skilled indeed, mm-hmm.
00_st_akane02_nomal
Akane: Hey, Reisha.
What is it?
00_st_akane02_nomal

Akane: Speaking of combat, you've fought all sorts of
monsters before, right? Tell me about the particularly
strong ones. I want to hear about a knight's valor!

Indeed. There have been many formidable foes, but it's
difficult to compare their strength.

Since each one has different characteristics, I try not to
lump them all together as 'monsters'...
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: You make things too complicated. Just give me a
simple answer.

Then how about I tell you about the monster that left an
impression on me, the one I pay particular attention to when
fighting?
00_st_akane02_nomal
Akane: Yeah, yeah, that's what I'm talking about!
00_st_akane02_smile

Akane: An orc? A horde of goblins? A ghoul or a wolf? Maybe
even a dragon!?

I hate to disappoint you, but the one I'm most cautious
about when fighting is the "Slime."
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: Huh? Slime? Don't be ridiculous. That's like the
epitome of weak monsters.
That may be true for the average adventurer.

But as I said, since each one has different characteristics,
we can't generalize them. Slimes have particularly bad
compatibility with knights. They're known as the bane of
knights.

Specifically, it's about knight equipment. Especially when
fully armored with plate armor.
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: Why's that? With your trusty armor and shield to
block attacks and a sword or spear to finish them off, it
should be over in no time.
I thought the same until I actually fought one.

However, some slimes with a strong predatory instinct will
scatter and spread their bodies desperately when cornered,
raining down on us to cover us completely.
00_st_akane02_anger
Akane: Uh-huh, and then what?

As you know, knights are far more heavily equipped than the
average adventurer. Full plate armor can be quite heavy.

Unlike equipment that prioritizes mobility and allows for
quick movements, it's difficult to dodge attacks that come
not as points or lines but as surfaces.

And then the slime that sticks to the body uses its liquid
form to infiltrate through the gaps in the armor. This is
troublesome for knights.

If slime slips inside through the gaps in the armor, it's
difficult to force it out with external impacts. What can be
done with cloth or leather equipment becomes impossible with
metal.

What's worse is that knight armor is cumbersome to put on
and take off. It's difficult to just strip it off and get
rid of the slime if it gets inside.
00_st_akane02_anger
Akane: Ugh... Just imagining it makes me feel sick...

And then the slime moves around inside the armor while
emitting a rotten smell. The sensation of it crawling all
over one's body is something I'd rather not think about. It
moves inside like wine leisurely flowing in a bottle,
untouchable from the outside.
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: Don't compare it to food! It's making me lose my
appetite!!

And of course, the slime moving inside the armor aims for
the respiratory organs in the head.

Clogging up the nose and mouth is their surefire hunting
strategy. You might think you can just shake them off with
your hands, but it's different for knights. If it were a
simple helm, there might be a way to deal with it...
00_st_akane02_serious
Akane: Oh, right! The helmet...!

Exactly. Imagine if slime invaded inside a metal helmet that
covers the entire face.

No matter how much you claw at the outside, it's already too
late. It takes time to remove it, and as the amount of slime
increases, pressure makes it impossible to take off from the
head easily.
Can you imagine drowning on land? It's hellish.
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: Eek...!! Stop it already!!! I just wanted to hear
about bravery, not ghost stories...!

I myself made such a blunder during my apprentice days. The
moment I felt danger as it crawled up inside my armor and
when it entered my metal helmet, I cursed my own
inexperience. And by the time slime started invading every
orifice on my face, I had long since passed out.

The moment it crawled up inside my armor, I realized the
danger. When it entered my metal helmet, I cursed my own
inexperience. And by the time slime started invading every
orifice on my face, I had long since passed out.

Thanks to the help of those around me, it wasn't fatal, but
if I had been alone... Ever since then, even seeing a
'birdlime' toy that children play with would send shivers
down my spine.
00_st_akane02_anger

Akane: Eek...!! Stop it already!!! I don't want to hear
anymore~~~~~~!!!!!!!

To prevent that, these days they carve demon-repelling
symbols inside helmets... Hey, Akane!

I was going to teach you how to remove slime when it gets
into your ears next, but really... You ask to hear the story
and then run away when you don't want to listen. What a busy
person.

(Ever since escaping the mining shaft, she's been
considerate like this, trying to cheer me up as I've been
downcast.)

(She's quite the accomplished human. It's embarrassing to
always be taken care of, but for now, I'll indulge a little
in her kindness.)

Hey, wait up!! If it's a race, I won't lose either!! Hah hah
hah!!
02_ev_interlude_akane_01

Thank you for listening. Please continue to enjoy the main
story.
